description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/senml/senml.c
Lines: 100-106, 155-161

CATEGORY: MEMORY - Uninitialized Read (Latent)

In senml_add_float() and senml_add_bool(), the record struct is not zeroed before use:

  struct senml_record *rec = &pack->records[pack->record_count++];
  rec->name = name;
  rec->unit = unit;
  rec->type = SENML_VALUE_FLOAT;
  rec->value.f = value;
  rec->has_time = false;  // time_offset NOT initialized

The time_offset field contains garbage from whatever was in the array slot before.

While has_time=false should prevent encode_record() from reading time_offset (line 247-251), this is fragile:
1. If logic ever changes to check time_offset first, it reads uninitialized memory
2. Static analyzers and sanitizers may flag this
3. Defense in depth requires zeroing unused fields

Note: senml_add_float_t() correctly initializes time_offset (line 133).

FIX: Either zero the record before use, or explicitly set time_offset = 0:
  rec->time_offset = 0;
  rec->has_time = false;
